The following sample shows how to use WindowsMediaPlayerClass class.  You should simply create new class instance and cast it to WindowsMediaPlayer interface.  After this you can call interface methods and access its properties: 
            WindowsMediaPlayer A = (WindowsMediaPlayer) new WindowsMediaPlayerClass();
            A.[method name]();  A.[property name] = [value]; [variable] = A.[property name];

